Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[Highly recommended reading: In addition to the grave concerns over sexual abuse taken from the Guardian article cited above, the Daily Mail report contains a timeline of Ebola cases and deaths in the DRC and several excellent tables. It presents a figure demonstrating that "the rate of infection and death from Ebola has been rising since the outbreak began in August last year [2018]; it took more than 2 months (5 Aug-21 Oct 2018) for the 1st 200 cases to be confirmed, then 272 people were infected between 4 Nov and 25 Dec 2018."

A table shows "The history of Ebola in the Democratic Republic of Congo since the killer virus was 1st discovered there in 1976," including year, cases, deaths, death %, strain, location. The case fatality rate ranges from 36% (Bundibugyo, Orientale, 2012) to 88% (Zaire, Yambuku, 1976). There is a single fatal Zaire case in Tandala in 1977 (100% CFR).

A final figure has data on which countries were struck down by Ebola during the 2014-16 epidemic. The range of case fatalities is from 28% in Sierra Leone to 67% in Guinea. The figures are from CDC. - Mod.LK]

